## 📄 Week 4 Summary (Data Visualization)
In Week 4, I learned how to visualize data using Python libraries such as Matplotlib and Seaborn. Data visualization is important because it helps in understanding patterns, trends, and relationships within data in a clear and meaningful way.
I studied different types of plots such as line plots, scatter plots, bar charts, and histograms using Matplotlib. These plots helped in representing data distributions and comparisons effectively. With Seaborn, I explored advanced visualizations like pair plots and heatmaps, which provide deeper insights into relationships between multiple features in a dataset.
During hands-on practice, I created various graphs to analyze datasets and understand how different variables are related. I also learned how to customize plots by adding titles, labels, and legends to make them more informative and visually appealing.
As part of the client project, I developed a basic dashboard that included multiple visualizations such as scatter plots, histograms, and correlation heatmaps. This helped in identifying relationships between features and understanding data behavior more clearly.
Overall, this week enhanced my ability to present data visually and draw meaningful conclusions. It also prepared me for more advanced data analysis and machine learning tasks.
